canonical:
  title: 送門生郭正言儀出按江陵
  author: 李仁復
  language: lzh
  text: 宵旰憂民日郞官奉使秋皁囊封暫輟紅旆挽難留邊靜無虛警山高有勝遊君看東海水早晚我乘桴
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 送門生郭正言儀出按江陵
  author: 李仁復
  language: lzh
  text: 宵旰憂民日。郞官奉使秋。皁囊封暫輟。紅旆挽難留。邊靜無虛警。山高有勝遊。君看東海水。早晚我乘桴。
korean:
  title: 강릉 안찰로 나가는 문생 정언 곽의를 보내며
  author: 이인복
  language: kor
  text: |-
    소한으로 백성을 걱정하는 날이여
    낭관이 사명 띠고 가는 때이어라
    조랑을 봉해 올리던 것 잠깐 멈추고
    붉은 깃발은 만류해도 머물기 어렵네
    변방이 고요하니 경보가 없고
    산이 높으매 올라가 놀 만하리
    자네 동해물을 보게
    조만간 나도 뗏목을 타겠네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0130_010_0070&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 나도 뗏목을 타겠네 : '
    value: 공자(孔子)가, “도(道)가 행하여지지 않는다. 나는 뗏목을 타고 바다에 떠서 가리라.” 하였다.
english:
  title: Sending Off My Student Guo Zhengyan on His Inspection Tour to Jiangling
  author: Lee In-bok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Through cold and bitter days I worry for the people,
    while you, an official, set forth on your autumn mission.
    The black leather satchel I seal away for now—
    the crimson banner, though we wish to hold it back, cannot stay.

    The borderlands rest in quiet, no false alarms,
    the high mountains offer pleasant heights to roam.
    When you gaze upon the eastern sea's waters,
    soon enough I too shall take my raft and drift away.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'The final couplet alludes to Confucius, who said: "Since the Way does not prevail in the world, I shall take a raft and drift upon the sea." It expresses the poet''s own resignation should virtue and righteousness fail to flourish.'
